name: Debugging in RStudio
description:
• What we'll do
When you are building R scripts and documents, it can be challenging to figure out what went wrong when the code behaves in unexpected ways. Fortunately, there are excellent tools built into R and RStudio that can make debugging easier. This talk will explore those tools, including: using base R functions for debugging, tracing techniques, setting breakpoints in RStudio, understanding debug mode, and troubleshooting more complicated sources like packages and Shiny applications.

• What to bring
Charged laptop and your enthusiasm!

• Important to know

This meetup is not appropriate for very beginner level R users, we expect you to be familiar with fundamental R objects and functions.

Parking: Park in any spot marked "Reserved for the Columbus Collaboratory". There should be more than enough available- all are free. If you find that these spots are filled - park anywhere in surrounding lots and Katie will give you a day pass for your dashboard.

Call Katie if any issues finding it (440-452-6423).
Directions and map also available here:
http://columbuscollaboratory.com/Contact

name: 3º Meetup R-Ladies Rio
description:
Damos sequência aos nossos meetups sobre R e suas aplicações!

Somente participantes com fotos, que informem documento de identificação ( RG ou CPF ) poderão acessar o evento.

Teremos palestras sobre uso de R na Física e no Direito. Porque R é para todos os domínios de conhecimento. ;) 

R na Fisica

Contaremos com a Dra Clemencia Mora, que irá palestrar sobre o R em aplicações na Física.

Clemencia Mora Herrera é doutora em ciências com menção em Física pela Universidade de Genebra, Suíça, na área de Física  Experimental de Altas Energias. Sua tese foi sobre a produção de életrons provenientes de decaimentos de hádrons de sabor pesado  nas primeiras colisões de prótons no LHC, medidas pelo experimento ATLAS. Possui Bacharelado em Astronomia e Mestrado em ciências com menção em Física pela PUC-Chile, e pós-doutorado no CBPF para formar parte do grupo do  experimento CMS no LHC. Atualmente é professora adjunta do Departamento de Física Nuclear e Altas Energias da UERJ onde desenvolve sua pesquisa a procura de física além do modelo padrão em eventos de produção exclusiva  com o experimento CMS. 

E com o expertise da economista  Helena Riveiro Fernandes,que irá nos falar sobre:

Análise Envoltória de Dados  com o pacote Benchmarking
A Eficiência dos Juizados Especiais

Helena Riveiro Fernandes é mestre em ciências econômicas pela Universidade do Estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sua dissertação foi sobre o nível de eficiência nos juizados especiais. Possui Bacharelado em ciências econômicas pela PUC-Rio e pós-graduação em Administração pública pela FGV-rio.

Atualmente trabalha como Assistente de pesquisa ll no IPEA onde auxilia em projetos de pesquisa de interesse nacional relacionados à produtividade setorial.

name: Take your R scripts to a new planet: Jupyter notebooks with R!
description:
T'agradaria aprendre a combinar els teus scripts de R amb text enriquit, explicacions de cada pas i les gràfiques corresponents? En aquesta trobada utilitzarem R mitjançant l’aplicació de Jupyter Notebook. 


https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/7388996?s=400&v=4

La sessió serà una introducció a aquesta útil eina de treball, començant des dels passos de instal·lació, exemples bàsics fins a casos més sofisticats d’anàlisi utilitzant dades científiques.


Tot i que donarem instruccions a l’aula, recomanem que us instal·leu anaconda prèviament. Necessitareu:

• Go to https://www.anaconda.com/download and download the appropriate version of anaconda. Then execute the downloaded sh script to install.  

• Create a new, specific R environment and install the essential r packages and the IRKernel by typing at the terminal:  conda create -n my_r_env_name -c r r-essentials r-irkernel  

• Activate the environment by typing at the terminal: source activate my_r_env_name 

• Install the nb_conda package by typing at the terminal: conda install nb_conda 

• Install the plotting libraries required for our examples: conda install r-gplots r-ggplot2

Ens veiem ben aviat!

____ English version ______________________


Would you like to learn how to combine your R scripts with enriched text explanations and graphs? In this meetup, we will run R code through the Jupyter Notebook app. 

https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/7388996?s=400&v=4

This will be an introduction to this tool, starting from installation and setup and basic examples, and building up to more sophisticated examples with using scientific data.


Although we will give setup instructions there, it is recommended that you install anaconda in advance to the meetup. You will need to:

• Go to https://www.anaconda.com/download and download the appropriate version of anaconda. Then execute the downloaded sh script to install.  

• Create a new, specific R environment and install the essential r packages and the IRKernel by typing at the terminal:  conda create -n my_r_env_name -c r r-essentials r-irkernel  

• Activate the environment by typing at the terminal: source activate my_r_env_name 

• Install the nb_conda package by typing at the terminal: conda install nb_conda 

•  Install the plotting libraries required for our example: r-gplots and r-ggplot2


See you all there!

name: R Markdown y cierre del año!
description:
Se viene el último evento del año! Y tenemos el taller de R Markdown para cerrar con broche de oro!!!

R Markdown permite escribir informes reproducibles y dinámicos con R.  Podés usarlo para incluir código R y resultados en presentaciones, documentos pdf, html, Word y mas. Este taller está pensado desde un nivel básico-intermedio, así que no te preocupes si recién empiezas a codear en R.  Para aprovecharlo traé tu laptop con R y RStudio instalados (para más info de cómo hacer esto:https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B0X9hdtcUykTdy1ZaVM3S3hxQ0k.

Si creés que te vendría bien una intro a R o un repaso antes de venir, hacé click aquí para ir al repositorio donde encontrarás todos los materiales de nuestros encuentros anteriores.

Después del taller tendremos un espacio reservado para hacer sociales, así nos conocemos entre todxs y podemos compartir ideas para el próximo año. Este se realizará en el restaurant del Museo Evita, el consumo aprox. es de 150 pesos y además habrá torta especial de R-Ladies para todxs!

Se vienen más detalles en unos días, por lo pronto revisá tu agenda y reservá tu lugar en el taller! Si confirmás asistencia pero luego no podés asistir, te pedimos por favor que dejes tu lugar disponible para otra persona ya que el espacio es limitado. Y si no podés asistir, el día de la reunión anunciaremos el acceso al streaming del evento. 


Cualquier consulta no dudes en escribirnos por meetup, slack o fb.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

****El evento se realizará en el auditorio del Museo Evita, para llegar se toma la entrada del restaurant, el auditorio está subiendo al escalera que está a la derecha en el patio del restaurant****


*** Para asegurarte que tu notebook está lista para trabajar en el taller, si es posible, por favor, actualizá tu versión de R y RStudio. También para instalar los paquetes necesarios para el taller, desde RStudio seguí estos pasos:


1) File -> New file -> R Markdown...


2) Se abrirá un cuadro de diálogo, hacé clic en "Ok"


3) Se abrirá un script de R "Untitled 1", apretá Ctrl+Shift+K


4) Pedirá grabar el archivo, ponéle un nombre y hacé clic en "Ok"


5) Si necesitás instalar paquetes, RStudio te avisará y lo hará. Si todo va bien, al final se abrirá una ventana mostrando un documento que comienza con la palabra "Untitled". Cerrá todo, ya estás lista para el taller.


Si surge algún problema durante este proceso, avisános por meetup, Slack o llegá un ratito antes al taller así tratamos de solucionarlo entre todas****

Saludos!

Beginner Statistic workshop in R

Speaker: Navid Nobani

In this workshop you will learn what is statistics, how it can be useful for data analysis and why as a data scientist you need to learn it. The topics are fundamental concepts, and are focused on:

- What are variable types in data and how to deal with them


- How to measure variability and central tendency of data

- How to choose graphical presentation types based on types of variables


- Linear & regression modeling

Language: Examples & exercises will be in R

Prerequisites: Having laptop is not mandatory

Target Audience: Beginners level

Bio: Navid is a data scientist at Prometeon Tyre Group. He has a background in Industrial Engineering and is working in the data science field since 2015. He uses R and Python in his daily activities to solve business problems in the marketing area.


If you are interested, don’t hesitate to join us & spread the event to your friends too. We are looking forward to meet up with you!

name: Lightning Talks
description:
Come join the R-Ladies in our first ever Lightning Talks event. In this fun, informal setting, participants have approximately 3 to 5 minutes to speak about their research, work, or a puzzle they're trying to solve - anything goes! R-related presentations are a bonus but not necessary! Our goal is to 1) provide a space to learn about the others in our community and 2) exchange ideas about methodologies, interests, and the tools we all are using.

IMPORTANT FOR PRESENTERS:

In addition to RSVPing on our MeetUp page, please ALSO complete this form (https://goo.gl/forms/LeoSGYLzdgrXthks2) by December 23 to help us with scheduling and to let us know important pieces of information.

This is not meant to be a high-stakes presentation event - just a chance to share our projects with each other and learn a little about the questions each of us are asking in our own work and the tools we're using to answer them. As usual, we will head out for food and drinks following the event (drinks and apps for presenters are on us!)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NB: Please note that, in keeping with the global R-Ladies mission, R-Ladies London, Ontario will prioritize female leadership and participation. All interested people (regardless of gender) are welcome to RSVP to our events. However, in the event that we receive a greater amount of presenter interest than we feel is manageable for the space/time, we will prioritize female presenters.

name: Collaborative Data Science with Kaggle Kernels and Datasets
description:
RLadies Los Angeles and LA Women Who Code are excited to present


Collaborative Data Science with Kaggle Kernels and Datasets

by Megan Risdal

Code and data sharing in collaboration with others is integral to open data science. On Kaggle, the world’s largest online data science community, users use Kernels as a platform to share and execute reproducible code and Datasets to access, analyze, and maintain public data projects. Since the introduction of Kernels in 2015, users have written tens of thousand of kernels in R, Python, and Julia. And in the past year, users and organizations have published over 2,000 public datasets. Over this time, Kernels and Datasets have transformed how the data science community tackles machine learning problems, collaborates, and learns. In this talk, Megan Risdal uses community metrics and insights to share what Kernels and Datasets have taught Kaggle about collaborative data science. 

Megan is a Community Advocate and Data Scientist at Kaggle. She holds master’s degrees in linguistics from UCLA and North Carolina State University.

Where: Google Venice, 400 Hampton Drive, Venice 90291

(Note: Enter through the gate on Sunset here: https://goo.gl/QwgtQf).

When: Tuesday October 17th, 2017

6.00: Doors open, food and drinks served. 

7.00: Talk start. 

8.00: Talk end. 

Unfortunately parking will not be provided, but there are public parking lots close by.

Food and drinks will be provided. 

Bring photo ID - we cannot admit without it. Please do not attend if you are not on the list of registered attendees. 

Please be Googley, and if you’re not going to be able to attend, cancel so that someone else can attend instead.

name: Data Visualization with ggplot2 Book Club
description:
• What we'll do
Join us for an interactive “book club” based on R for Data Science Chapter 3 (link: http://r4ds.had.co.nz/data-visualisation.html). Navigating data visualization in R can be a complicated journey – from choosing a package and function to actually exporting and saving a graph. Beginners and experts alike can benefit from talking about the common bottlenecks to making great graphs in R.

Agenda:
6:00-6:30: Networking, eating, announcements
6:30-7:00: Chapter discussion and troubleshooting common questions and problems
7:00-7:30: Expand to “real” data using example data from opendataphilly.org
7:30: Lightning talk – R package of the day

Once again, we are being hosted by the awesome people at MakeOffices! Thank you MakeOffices for allowing us to use the space. Please check them out: https://makeoffices.com

When you arrive at Two Commerce Square (20th & Market), you will need to check in with the security desk before heading up to the 25th floor. It helps if you can RSVP with us, so we can give an accurate guest list to the security desk.

We are also supported by RStudio (https://www.rstudio.com). RStudio has a mission to provide the most widely used open source and enterprise-ready professional software for the R statistical computing environment. These tools further the cause of equipping everyone, regardless of means, to participate in a global economy that increasingly rewards data literacy.

• What to bring
Bring a laptop with R and RStudio installed. We recommend everyone read the chapter ahead of time and work through the exercises.

• Important to know
If you haven't been to an R-Ladies event, fill out our survey! http://bit.ly/rladies-survey
We will then add you to our Slack, where we can answer questions.

name: Welcome to R-Ladies Montenegro!
description:
R-Ladies Montenegro is happy to announce our 1st MeetUp for 25 August 2017 at 19:00 in Herceg Novi (Caffe Bar Porto).

If you would like to learn R and share your experience of working in R or would just like to find out what is R this would be a perfect place for you. It doesn't matter whether you are a beginner or an experienced R coder, come and join us! 

In our first meeting we will talk about why R is language of choice for many data scientists through a series of demonstrations and hands on exercises. You will be able to learn some of the fundamental concepts of R: basic use of R/RStudio console, inputting and importing different data types, record keeping, graphs etc. We will conclude our first meeting by showing how to create reproducible R-Markdown documents. If you have a laptop bring it with you so we can do some R coding together. We will show you how to install R and RStudio if you haven’t already done so.

If any of you would like to present short demos of R code you are using in your projects or R packages please get in touch and we will include it in our programme.

The final programme will be announced a few days prior to the meeting.

We are looking forward to seeing you all…

> #---------------------------------------------------------------------

R-Ladies Montenegro sa zadovoljstvom najavljuju naš prvi MeetUp 25. avgusta 2017. u 19h u Herceg Novom (Caffe Bar Porto).

Ako želite naučiti R, podeliti svoje iskustvo u korišćenju R-a, ili biste samo želeli saznati što je to R, ovo će biti savršeno mesto za vas. Nije važno da li ste početnik ili iskusan R koder, dođite i pridružite nam se!

Na našem prvom sastanku razgovaraćemo o tome zašto je jezik R izbor za mnoge data scientist-e kroz niz demonstracija i konkretnih vežbi. Moći ćete naučiti neke od osnovnih pojmova R-a, osnovnu upotrebu R/RStudio programa: unos i snimanje različitih vrsta podataka, grafički prikaz itd. Završi ćemo naš prvi sastanak tako što ćemo prikazati kako kreirati reproducibilni R-Markdown dokument. Ako imate laptop, donesite ga tako da možemo R-kodirati zajedno. Ako nemate R i RStudio na svom kompjuteru, pomoći ćemo vam da ih instalirate.

Ako neko od vas želi demonstrirati svoj projekat i kod u R-u, ili svoj R-paket, molimo da nas kontaktirate kako bi smo vas uključili u programsku šemu.

Konačna programska šema biće objavljena nekoliko dana pre sastanka.

Unapred se radujemo našem susretu…

name: Presentación de R-Ladies y Aplicaciones de R en Santa Rosa
description:
El ITES nos invitó a dar una charla para los estudiantes de la Tecnicatura Superior en Desarrollo de Software y al público en general este jueves 22 de junio a partir de las 21:30 hs.

Las disertantes son la Magister en Explotación de Datos y Gestión de Conocimiento, Investigadora del INTA, Yanina Bellini Saibene y la Estudiante de Doctorado en Ciencias Agrarias de la UBA Marina Cook ambas organizadoras de RLadies Santa Rosa. En primer lugar se expondrá sobre Agro Minería de Datos: en un mundo que necesita cada vez mas alimentos, producir más y mejor, cuidando la salud y el medio ambiente, es uno de los desafíos del sector agropecuario. La minería de datos es una de las herramientas que puede ayudar en este objetivo al permitir analizar y modelar los sistemas productivos. Se informará sobre el uso de Data Mining en INTA y como R les ayuda en esa tarea.


En la segunda parte se referirán a Modelos Mixtos: los avances en informática permitieron desarrollar modelos más complejos y realistas para el análisis de datos. Nos mostrarán qué modelos usan y por qué; por qué usar R y que ventajas ofrece.

Finalmente se hablará sobre RLadies: presentaremos el capitulo Santa Rosa de esta organización mundial que busca disminuir la brecha de género en las personas que usan R.


Los espermos!!!

name: Fouille de textes avec R: expression régulier.
description:
Dans ce meetup le theme est la fouille de textes. Une presentation sur comme manipuler de textes avec le function basic de R (grep, grepl, etc...) et avec le package stringr serait fait. Nous verrons comment extraire de valeur numérique et des tables dans un text. La presentation serait fait par Rita Giordano.

For this meetup will be presented a talk on how to manipulate string with R using the basic function as grep and the packages stringr. We will see how to extract numerical value and tables from a text file. The presentation will be performed by Rita Giordano.

name: R Absolute Beginners Workshop (Again!)
description:
****please register via Eventbrite link below****

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/r-absolute-beginners-workshop-again-tickets-36673157401?aff=es2


Our first Absolute Beginners Workshop sold out, so R-Ladies will run a second August session for Absolute R Beginners!


Want to learn R? You have come to the right place because this time R-Ladies Adelaide offer you an opportunity to get yourself involved into R - the language of data! Come and spend Thursday evening with R-Ladies at Microsoft Innovation Centre on the 24th of August.


If you have never worked with R before and want to start, this event is for you! It is expected that all attendees will arrive with a laptop (and chargers), and R and RStudio installed on their computers (please follow the instructions here: http://www.ics.uci.edu/~jutts/110/InstallingRandRStudio.pdf). We will walk you through the R programming basics, help with FAQs, point you to relevant learning resources, and any other fundamental R questions you may have!

PROGRAM:

Timings: 5.30 doors open, lightning talk starts 5.40, the workshop starts 6 pm.

WHAT IS COVERED:

Getting around R

Types of data and basic manipulations

Graphics in R


P.S. RLadies Adelaide is part of the international organization RLadies Global and aims to encourage more women to get involved in their local programming communities. We encourage all genders to attend our events, and aim always to create a welcoming environment. All talks and workshops at RLadies will be presented by women, in order to strengthen the presence of women in the coding community. We hope to see you at our next event!
